Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.83,0:00:07.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}除了我们生活的这个层次  还有其它的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We live on one level of existence, but there are others.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.43,0:00:12.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到处充满了隐藏着的其它维度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These hidden dimensions of reality are everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.12,0:00:14.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从许多光年以外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Far away, across the light years.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.67,0:00:15.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到我们的脚下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Beneath our feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.91,0:00:19.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至在我们的体内\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And even inside you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.55,0:00:22.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们由原子组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are made of atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.94,0:00:25.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们眼睛中的原子数量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are more atoms in your eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.85,0:00:29.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比已知宇宙中所有星系的星星数量还多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than there are stars and all the galaxies of the known universe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:36.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上述情况也适用于任何\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same is true of any solid object
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.18,0:00:38.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比你的指尖稍大的实体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}larger than the tip of your little finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.92,0:00:42.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我由30万亿亿亿复杂排列的原子组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm a collection of three billion, billion, billion
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.79,0:00:45.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我是名叫尼尔・德葛拉司・泰森的原子组合体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}intricately arranged atoms called Neil Degrasse Tyson.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.73,0:00:50.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你们也是一样  只是名字不同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You are a similar collection with a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.60,0:00:52.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们通常不会这么认为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't usually think of ourselves this way
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.13,0:00:56.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为这个级别的存在超过了我们感官的范畴\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because that level of reality lies beyond the realm of our senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.20,0:00:58.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们不会就此停止\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we're not gonna let that stop us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.44,0:01:01.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们还要继续探究\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can go deeper into the wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.36,0:02:39.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第六集
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:49.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子使所有事情变得有生气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Atoms let matter do funny things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.66,0:02:52.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要了解水 你需要知道它的原子规律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To understand water, you need to know what its atoms are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.62,0:02:55.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个水分子都是由\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every molecule of water is composed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.16,0:02:56.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}两个小小的氢原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of two tiny hydrogen atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:59.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}附着在一个大的氧原子上组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}attached to a larger oxygen atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:01.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此我们称之为 一氧化二氢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why we call it H20.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.50,0:03:04.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果温度不冷不热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it's not too hot or too cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.64,0:03:07.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}分子们可以相互翻滚穿行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the molecules can slide and tumble past each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.34,0:03:09.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}分子间还是有一些的粘滞性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's still some stickiness between the molecules,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:12.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是不足以让它们变的紧密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not enough to lock them into a rigid solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:15.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是液体的特性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what makes something a liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:17.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳将水加热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sun warms the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.35,0:03:18.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给它更多的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And with more energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.75,0:03:20.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}分子们移动加快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the molecules move faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:22.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}温度就是这样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's all that temperature is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:24.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当分子运到快到足以\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those molecules are moving fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:27.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}打破彼此间脆弱的联系时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to break the weak bonds that hold them to their neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.66,0:03:29.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是蒸发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's evaporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:31.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们呼吸的空气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The air we breathe is made of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.50,0:03:33.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是由氮和氧的分子组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}nitrogen and oxygen molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:37.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}再加一些水蒸气和二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a scattering of water vapor and carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.33,0:03:39.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}小心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incoming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:41.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是冷凝\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's condensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:46.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}露珠就是冷凝战胜蒸发的胜利果实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A dewdrop is the momentary triumph of condensation over evaporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:48.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种现象持续下去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And while it lasts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.11,0:03:51.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就是一个小宇宙 包含它自己的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's a little cosmos with its own worlds...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.58,0:03:54.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生物 戏剧性的事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creatures, drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:58.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了探索这滴露珠的广阔领域\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To explore the far-flung realms of this dewdrop
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.39,0:03:59.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们需要一艘船\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're gonna need a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.06,0:04:02.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}配上两种引擎\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One with twin engines...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.03,0:04:05.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学和想象力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}science and imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.37,0:04:13.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是单细胞的草履虫\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a single-celled paramecium,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.30,0:04:18.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是在露珠中游荡中众多娴熟的猎人之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of a multitude of skilled hunter-warriors that roam the dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.74,0:04:21.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是它们同时也是猎物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they, too, are hunted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.11,0:04:25.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}长颈虫  草履虫的死敌\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Dileptus. The paramecium's mortal enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:29.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}草履虫或许可以幸运的直接击杀\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The paramecium might get lucky and score a direct hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.72,0:04:31.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就算不能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even if it doesn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:33.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}齐射攻击造成的后座力拉开了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the recoil from the barrage will put some distance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.99,0:04:35.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}草履虫与攻击者之间的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the paramecium and its attacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.59,0:04:40.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我还能说些什么呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What can I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.89,0:04:42.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是露珠内的生活\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's life in the dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.74,0:04:57.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个小家伙是水熊虫\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That little guy is tardigrade,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:05:00.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一种比针尖还小的动物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an animal smaller than the head of a pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:05.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可别小看它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Don't underestimate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.12,0:05:08.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}水熊虫在这个星球上的历史比我们的还长久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tardigrades have been living on this planet a lot longer than we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.42,0:05:11.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们已存在地球上大约5亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About 500 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:15.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和我们的数量比例\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For every one of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.70,0:05:18.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}至少是1比10亿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's at least a billion of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.93,0:05:24.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们可以在地球上任何地方生存\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can make a living anywhere on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:27.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在最高的寒冷的山峰顶端\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the frigid peaks of the tallest mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:29.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在喷发的火山口里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the cauldrons of erupting volcanoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.81,0:05:32.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在大洋的底部\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in the deep ocean vents at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.34,0:05:33.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}水熊虫是如此的坚强\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tardigrades are so tough,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.78,0:05:37.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们可以在真空中生存\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can survive naked in the vacuum of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:41.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们经历了最近五次的大灭绝\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've survived all five of the most recent mass extinctions on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:45.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果外星人认为地球是水熊虫的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A visitor from another world could be forgiven
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.19,0:05:48.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是绝对可以原谅的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for thinking of earth as the planet of the tardigrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.33,0:05:56.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果还要看这滴露珠的其它地方 最好继续往前走\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we're ever gonna get to the bottom of this dewdrop better get a move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.80,0:06:01.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每片叶子和苔藓\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every leaf and tiny clump of moss
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.97,0:06:03.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都有成千上万的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has hundreds of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:06.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}显微镜才能看见的嘴巴 称为气孔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of microscopic mouths called Stomata.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.48,0:06:08.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}植物通过它们呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Plants breathe through them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.48,0:06:09.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}吸入二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}taking in carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.98,0:06:12.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}呼出我们赖以生存的氧气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and exhaling the oxygen that we need to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.85,0:06:15.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上可以没有我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The plants can survive without us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.19,0:06:17.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们还有其它动物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we and all the other animals...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:20.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}离开它们就死翘翘了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'd be toast without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.59,0:06:22.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球通过阳光获取食物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The plants make food out of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.83,0:06:25.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们动物做不到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We animals can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.23,0:06:27.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想看它们是怎么做到的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To see how they do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:28.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们还要潜的更深\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we have to go deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.73,0:06:30.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把我们变小大约1千倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}make ourselves about a thousand times smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.83,0:06:33.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才能进入它们的宝库\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to get into their treasure house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.60,0:06:35.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们把好东西都藏在里面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the place where they keep the good stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.37,0:06:37.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是叶绿素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the chlorophyll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.27,0:06:41.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它虽然是个分子 可是却能负责把阳光转换成能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the molecule that converts sunlight into energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:46.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个长方形都是一个植物细胞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every one of those rectangles is a plant cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.95,0:06:51.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有那些小绿车 那都是它的能量工厂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And those tiny green vehicles are its energy factories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.85,0:06:53.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们可以窃取它们的商业机密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we could steal their trade secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又能带来一次崭新的工业革命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would trigger a new industrial revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.03,0:06:57.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是要偷窥它们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But to spy on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.86,0:06:59.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们还得潜得更深\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're gonna need to go deeper still.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:17.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想象之舟这次又要将我们带去哪个截然不同的世界呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What alien world has the ship of the imagination carried us to this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:19.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是个宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the cosmos...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:23.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在露珠里面的宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Contained within a dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.39,0:07:26.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们现在做的就是工业间谍活动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're on an industrial espionage mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:28.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果想刺探叶绿体的商业机密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we can penetrate the trade secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.83,0:07:31.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}叶绿体里的制作过程\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the manufacturing process in that chloroplast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.73,0:07:34.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就当我们的全部未来就靠它了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}let's just say our whole future hangs in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:39.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}叶绿体利用阳光将水分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This chloroplast is using sunlight to break water molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:42.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}分解成氢原子和氧原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into atoms of hydrogen and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.04,0:07:46.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将氢气与二氧化碳结合产生糖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It combines the hydrogen with carbon dioxide to make sugar,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.05,0:07:49.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将氧气作为废气排出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and releases the oxygen as a waste product.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.38,0:07:52.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要一探究竟 我们还要潜的更深\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To see how it happens, we have to go even deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.25,0:07:53.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变得更小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}get even smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:57.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}小到原子级别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're talking atomic scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.16,0:07:58.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成功了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:02.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这条流水线是分子工业基地的核心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This assembly line is the heartof the molecular industrial complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.23,0:08:05.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在分子这个级别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the molecular level,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.23,0:08:07.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}速度快到我们看不到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}things happen too fast for us to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.26,0:08:09.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以我们必须让它们慢下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we'll have to slow them down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:11.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}放慢十亿倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about a billion times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:16.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些大分子就是二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those larger molecules are carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.84,0:08:18.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一个分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each one of them is made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.34,0:08:20.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由1个碳原子和2个氧原子组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of one carbon and two oxygen atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.24,0:08:23.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当阳光照射叶绿素的分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When sunlight strikes a green molecule of chlorophyll,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.45,0:08:26.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就会产生一系列的化学反应\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it sets in motion a series of chemical reactions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.62,0:08:28.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}分解水分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}breaking apart water molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.45,0:08:31.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}释放活泼的电子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and freeing energetic electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:35.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这只是日班的活\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's just the day shift,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:37.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只在日光注入能量时工作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when sunlight supplies the incoming stream of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.03,0:08:40.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一组不分昼夜的工作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a second shift that works day and night
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.00,0:08:43.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}利用预留的太阳能工作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}using the solar energy kept in reserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:48.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自由电子的能量开始工作了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy of the free electrons is put to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.10,0:08:52.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将二氧化碳与水中的氢结合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}combining carbon dioxide with hydrogen from the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.31,0:08:56.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}产生糖  用以储存太阳能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The end product is sugar,which stores the solar energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:08:59.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}叶绿体从事太阳能采集工作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The chloroplast is a three-billion-year-old
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.98,0:09:02.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}长达30亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}solar energy collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.52,0:09:05.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}微观世界的太阳能电池\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This sub-microscopic solar battery
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.29,0:09:07.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}驱动了所有的森林 田地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is what drives all the forests and the fields
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.82,0:09:10.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至是海中的浮游生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the plankton of the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.06,0:09:11.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有动物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.79,0:09:13.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.86,0:09:16.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳能的生物圈\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The solar-powered biosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.20,0:09:21.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比我们整个人类文明收集并处理的能量多出6倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}collects and processes six times more power than our entire civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:25.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们了解化学层面的光合作用工作原理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We understand on a chemical level how photosynthesis works.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.37,0:09:27.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以在实验室复制这样的过程\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can recreate the process in a laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.51,0:09:30.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们做不到植物这么好\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we're not as good at it as plants are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:32.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这并不奇怪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's not surprising,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.38,0:09:34.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为大自然已经这样工作几十亿年了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}considering nature has been at this for billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.81,0:09:36.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而我们才刚开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we've only just started.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.92,0:09:38.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们可以知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if we could figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:40.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光合作用的商业机密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the trade secrets of photosynthesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.75,0:09:44.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如今我们赖以生存的其它形式的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every of other source of energy we depend on today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.69,0:09:49.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}煤 石油 天然气都可以淘汰了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}coal, oil, natural gas would become obsolete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.76,0:09:52.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光合作用是终极绿色能源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Photosynthesis is the ultimate green power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.43,0:09:54.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它不会污染大气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It doesn't pollute the air
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.33,0:09:59.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}事实上 碳中和人造光合作用可以很大程度上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and is, in fact, carbon neutral. Artificial photosynthesis on a big enough scale
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:01.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}减少温室效应\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could reduce the greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:04.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所带来的气候变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's driving climate change in a dangerous direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:07.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这里开始蒸发了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Uh-oh, place is evaporating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.45,0:10:08.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}该撤了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Time to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.52,0:10:13.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}露珠的生命一闪即逝\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How fleeting is the life of a dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.02,0:10:17.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它在寒冷的夜里从稀薄的空气中凝结而成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It condenses from thin air in the cool of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.22,0:10:19.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}却在日出之后无影无踪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only to vanish with the heat of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:22.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的居民怎么办 水熊虫呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what of its inhabitants, the tardigrades?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.29,0:10:23.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们不会有事的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.03,0:10:26.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为它们可以几年不喝水\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can go without water for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.53,0:10:29.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很难想象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's hard to imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.43,0:10:31.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}覆盖地球表面的植物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but plants covered the surface of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:33.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几亿年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for hundreds of millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:37.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才开出第一朵花\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before they put forth their first flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.37,0:10:40.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大约1亿年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That was about a hundred million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.28,0:10:42.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恐龙灭绝前不久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shortly before the dinosaurs were wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.95,0:10:47.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时世界的颜色一定很单调\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our world must've been a relatively drab-looking place back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:50.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有绿色和褐色\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dominated by shades of green and brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.39,0:10:54.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是的那时是有大树和蕨类 还有其它的植物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yeah, there were giant trees and ferns and other plant life,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.72,0:10:56.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是没有紫色的鸢尾花\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not the purple of an iris
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.99,0:11:00.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也没有红色的玫瑰花\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or the crimson of a red, red rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.50,0:11:09.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}兰花是最早出现的花之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Orchids were among the first flowering species
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.57,0:11:13.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在它们有着最多的品种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to appear on earth, and they're the most diverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.18,0:11:20.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}达尔文特别痴迷马达加斯加的彗星兰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin was particularly fascinated by the comet orchid of Madagascar,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.32,0:11:28.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种花的花粉藏在一条又长又细的花径底部\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a flower whose pollen is hidden at the bottom of a very long, thin spur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:33.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}预测能力是验证一种理论的最好方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There can be no stronger test of an idea \than its predictive power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.19,0:11:36.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根据他的物竞天择的进化论基础\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the basis of his theory of evolution through natural selection
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:39.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}达尔文推测\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin speculated that somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.03,0:11:42.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在马达加斯加岛上 一定有一种会飞的昆虫\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the island of Madagascar, there must live flying insects
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.84,0:11:45.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}长着非常长的舌头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with extraordinarily lengthy tongues,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.97,0:11:47.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}长的足够接触到那些花粉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ones long enough to reach the pollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.84,0:11:51.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从没人看过这种动物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one had ever seen such a beast there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.45,0:11:53.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是达尔文坚信\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but Darwin insisted
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.18,0:11:56.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}肯定有这样的动物存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that an animal fitting this description must exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.52,0:11:58.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时相信他的人不多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Few people at the time believed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.29,0:12:01.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到50多年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It wasn't until more than 50 years later
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:04.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才证明了达尔文的猜测是正确的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Darwin was proven right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:11.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1903年 有一种被称为马岛长喙天蛾的蛾子在马达加斯加被发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1903, a huge hawk moth, called the Morgan's sphinx was discovered in Madagascar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.36,0:12:14.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}受到彗星兰花粉香味的吸引\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Attracted by the Comet Orchid's scent,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.90,0:12:19.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这蛾子用它1英尺长的口器吸食花粉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the moth slurps its pollen with its foot-long tongue,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.24,0:12:21.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和达尔文猜测的一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exactly as Darwin expected it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.41,0:12:29.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更令人惊奇的是 发现这种蛾子时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's even more amazing that the Morgan's sphinx was discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:35.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}马达加斯加岛上超过90%的雨林已经遭到破坏\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when you consider that more than 90% of Madagascar's rain forest had been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.59,0:12:38.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在达尔文著名的猜测多年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the years since Darwin's famous prediction,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.36,0:12:41.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种蛾子很有可能已经灭绝\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this moth species could have easily become extinct
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:44.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就和其它同类一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with all the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:47.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们每一个都是生命诗篇中的独特乐章\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every one of them a unique phrase of life's poetry,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:51.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由万古的进化写在原子中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}written in the atoms by eons of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:58.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}丁香花的芬芳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ah, the fragrance of lilacs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.93,0:13:00.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种香味\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's one of those scents
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.70,0:13:03.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让人不禁浮想翩翩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that triggers a whole constellation of associations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.77,0:13:06.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很久前的每个夏天都是如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all those junes of long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.91,0:13:08.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怎会如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how does that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:12.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}味道是怎么会让你的头脑中出现影像的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How does a smell prompt a movie to start running in your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:14.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那不是我们能看到的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not something we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.12,0:13:16.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有可能是象光一样的能量波吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could it be a wave of energy, like light?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.42,0:13:19.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还是一种微观粒子呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or is it some kind of microscopic particle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:21.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其实它是一种分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's actually a molecule.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.59,0:13:25.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每种味道 不论是来自烤焦的面包\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every odor we can sense, whether it comes from burnt toast
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.39,0:13:28.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还是汽油 或者一片丁香花\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gasoline, or a field of lilacs,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.90,0:13:31.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是一大片的分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a cloud of molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.13,0:13:34.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些分子有种特定的形状\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These molecules have particular shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.94,0:13:36.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当我吸入它们时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When I inhale them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.91,0:13:40.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们刺激我鼻子中一组特定的感受细胞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they stimulate a particular set of receptor cells in my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.91,0:13:45.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一种电子信号传递到我的大脑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An electrical signal then travels to my brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.15,0:13:47.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}告诉我这个味道是丁香花的香味\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which identifies the scent as lilac.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:53.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不同的分子携带不同的味道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Other scents are carried by different molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.25,0:13:55.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的形状也各异\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with different shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:13:59.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但当我闻到一朵花 或者篝火\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when I smell a flower or the smoke from a campfire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:00.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者机器的润滑油\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or the grease from a motor gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.96,0:14:04.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通常是涌现出大量的记忆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm often flooded with memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.07,0:14:11.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么花香这么简单的东西能够引起强烈的记忆呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why is it that a simple thing such as the scent of a flower can trigger powerful memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.44,0:14:17.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一定和我们的大脑进化方式有关\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has to do with the way our brains have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.94,0:14:20.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当大脑中的嗅神经受到刺激\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our sense of smell kicks in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.31,0:14:22.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的嗅觉开始工作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the olfactory nerve in our brain is stimulated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.68,0:14:28.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种神经就在扁桃体旁边\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That nerve is located very close to the amygdala,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.05,0:14:32.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是我们情感体验的组成部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a structure that is integral to our experience of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.99,0:14:36.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也很靠近海马体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's also very close to the Hippocampus,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.26,0:14:38.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}产生记忆的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which helps us form memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.87,0:14:44.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}神经网络将气味信号\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The network of neurons that carry the scent signal
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.20,0:14:47.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从我的鼻子传递到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from my nose to my brain has been fine-tuned
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.04,0:14:50.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我这经过上亿年进化的大脑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over hundreds of millions of years of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:54.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一种生存机制 给我们发出警告\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a survival mechanism that can alert us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.51,0:14:57.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们避开危险\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to danger or guide us to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.95,0:15:01.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你能提前发觉猎食者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you you can detect the predator
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.99,0:15:05.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他发动攻击前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before he's near enough to strike,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.02,0:15:07.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者在被大火困在森林前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or the fire before it traps you in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.36,0:15:09.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就会大大增加你的生存几率\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you have a much better chance to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.53,0:15:12.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后把你的基因传给下一代\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and pass on your genes to the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:20.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}花田里的迷人芬芳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That lovely scent from this field of flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:23.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发出一组独特的神经信号密码\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sets off a unique combination of nerve signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:27.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有这个密码可以打开我们大脑中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only that exact combination can crack the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:31.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}储存关于丁香花的记忆保险箱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the memory of lilacs is stored inside my brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.82,0:15:37.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}啥味道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wonder who they're for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.82,0:15:40.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们或许以后会知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe we'll find out later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.89,0:15:44.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但还有一个隐藏着的宇宙在等着我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But first, there's another hidden cosmos waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.04,0:16:09.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}植物们静静的呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The plants are softly breathing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.47,0:16:12.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}吸入二氧化碳分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inhaling molecules of carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.37,0:16:15.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}呼出氧气分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and exhaling molecules of oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.11,0:16:16.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和我相反\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And I'm doing the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.61,0:16:19.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与雪花和指纹不一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike snowflakes and fingerprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.98,0:16:21.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}同类的原子或分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}atoms or molecules of the same kind
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.78,0:16:24.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是完全的相同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are utterly identical to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:26.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每次吸气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With every breath we take,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.62,0:16:29.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们吸入的分子数量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we inhale as many molecules as there are stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.82,0:16:32.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和已知宇宙的所有星星数量一样多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in all the galaxies in the visible universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.39,0:16:35.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}呼出的气体与空气流通交换\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And every breath we exhale is circulated through the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.46,0:16:37.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在大地上逐渐混合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and mixed gradually across the continents,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.00,0:16:41.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让别人也可以呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it becomes available for others to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.97,0:16:43.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一起呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Breathe with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:57.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们大致吸入了1亿的分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We all just inhaled about 100 million molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.65,0:16:59.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些分子曾经被所有的前人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that once passed through the lungs of everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.85,0:17:01.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}呼吸过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who ever lived before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.92,0:17:05.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想想看 这种原子的再生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of it... This kind of atomic reincarnation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.12,0:17:07.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将我们与远古的祖先联系在一起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is another link to our distant ancestors,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.43,0:17:10.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括那些最初带领我们探索\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including those who first launched us on our explorations
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:13.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}未知宇宙的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the unseen universes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.13,0:17:16.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些宇宙就如同你我一样真实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These universes are as real as you or me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.60,0:17:18.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在我们的身边\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:25.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}曾经我们如梦初醒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was a moment when we awakened
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.71,0:17:28.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}开始用崭新的方法审视和思考\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a new way of thinking and seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:31.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是大约2500年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It happened about 2,500 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.82,0:17:33.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在希腊的小岛上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the Greek islands that lie
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:36.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}位于东方与西方文明之间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the empires of the east and west.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:41.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}商人 游客 水手们自由的融合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There, merchants, tourists and sailors freely mingled,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:44.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}交流各自关于伟人和神的传说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exchanging tales of great kings and gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.19,0:17:48.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在爱奥尼亚有个叫米利都的城市 就是今天的土耳其\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In Ionian cities and towns like Miletus, in what is now Turkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.70,0:17:50.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一些现代生活的最基本元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most fundamental elements
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.90,0:17:53.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那里出现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the way we live now first appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.24,0:18:01.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第一次对生活形式的重现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here, for the first time, reenactments of aspects of life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.54,0:18:04.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由专业人士创作并演绎\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}created and executed by professionals
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.51,0:18:09.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}期待可以深深感动观众的内心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the expectation of touching something deep within the hearts of the audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:12.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者只是逗他们开心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or just making them laugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.05,0:18:16.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}诞生了第一场演出 戏剧还有喜剧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first plays, dramas and comedies, were performed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:19.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一种极其崭新的概念\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here, also, was born a radical new idea:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.60,0:18:21.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}民治政府\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Government by the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.56,0:18:25.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从最初模糊的不完美的概念 到如今的民主\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first inklings, imperfect then as now, of a democracy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:30.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}普通民众也可以拥有某些权力的观念\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the notion that the ordinary citizen might possess certain rights
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.17,0:18:33.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那时 在这里诞生萌芽\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}come to us from this time and place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.64,0:18:37.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但在我看来 这个古代世界带给我们的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in my view, the most revolutionary innovation of all
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:41.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最革命性的创新观念是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to come to us from this ancient world was the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.85,0:18:47.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自然事件并不是众神给我们的惩罚或奖励\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that natural events were neither punishment nor reward from capricious gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:51.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大自然的规律不一定要用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The workings of nature could be explained
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.09,0:18:54.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超自然力量来解释\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without invoking the supernatural.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.26,0:18:56.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}表达出这种观念的第一人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first person to express this thought
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.56,0:18:58.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}名叫 泰利斯\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was a man named Thales.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.56,0:18:58.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}希腊哲学家
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:00.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当闪电或地震时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the thunder clapped or the earth quaked,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.80,0:19:05.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并不是因为我们的所作所为触怒了严厉的众神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was not because something you did had somehow displeased the very demanding gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.04,0:19:11.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是一种我们可以理解的自然过程的结果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No, it was the result of natural processes that we were capable of understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:15.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管没有任何记录他原话的书籍留存下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Though none of the books he is said to have written survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.15,0:19:19.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}泰利斯的思想光芒依然照耀我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thales kindled a flame that still burns to this day:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.22,0:19:21.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙运行的井井有条的原因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The very idea of cosmos out of chaos,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.29,0:19:27.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙由我们可以理解的自然法则控制的这种观念\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a universe governed by the order of natural laws that we can actually figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.69,0:19:32.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种伟大的观念在泰利斯的头脑中萌芽\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the epic adventure that began in the mind of Thales.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.43,0:19:36.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}仅仅在泰利斯身后100年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only a century following Thales' death,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.80,0:19:38.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又一个天才出现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another genius came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.40,0:19:40.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他与众不同的是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he, more than any other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.74,0:19:42.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第一个发现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was the first to discover the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:45.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们周围未知宇宙的存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the hidden universes that surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.01,0:19:50.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来自阿夫季拉的德谟克利特是为真正的科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Democritus of Abdera was a true scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:53.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}充满探索宇宙激情的男人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a man with a passionate desire to know the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.52,0:19:55.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也很会享受\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.32,0:19:58.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他曾说 "没有狂欢的生活\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the man who once said, "a life without parties
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.66,0:20:02.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}...就像没有尽头的漫漫长路"\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be like an endless road without an end."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.09,0:20:03.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就样吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You mean, that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.86,0:20:05.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就这么简单吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's all there is?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是虚无中的一堆原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just a bunch of atoms in a void?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.10,0:20:09.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然也\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:12.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你想想看\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:13.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个世界必然是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The world has to be made
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:17.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由虚无中无数的不可见的微粒组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of countless indivisible particles in a void.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.27,0:20:22.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}否则万物就不会移动 生长 被分离或改变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Otherwise, nothing could move or grow, be divided or changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.35,0:20:26.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果没有原子和容纳它们的空旷太空的话\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without atoms and empty space for them to move in,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:29.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个世界会变得像铁板一块 死气沉沉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the world would be solid, static and dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:32.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}别伤心了 少年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so don't be sad, my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.77,0:20:35.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想想那无尽的可能性吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just think of the infinite possibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.27,0:20:39.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由那些原子排列组合所带来的可能性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that arise from different arrangements of those atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.98,0:20:48.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向这杯的酒 还有酒中的原子们致敬\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's to the atoms in this cup and in this wine...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:51.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有它们带来的欢乐\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And to the laughter they make possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:56.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}当时的酒杯都由泥土烧制而成
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:58.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是用显微镜才能看到的矿物微粒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are microscopic mineral grains,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:56.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遍布酒杯的泥土\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dispersed through the Clay of the cup
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.36,0:21:00.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}晶体的一种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}different kinds of crystals,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.03,0:21:04.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个都有与众不同的原子结构\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each with its own distinctive atomic architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:07.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}矿物结构很精妙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mineral structures are exquisite,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.13,0:21:10.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是它们的结构形式有限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they have a limited repertoire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.14,0:21:13.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一粒石英就是一个由3个相同原子组成的晶格集合体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A grain of quartz is a lattice of the same three atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:17.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有变化 不断重复\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}repeated, without variation, over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.15,0:21:22.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使是相对复杂的矿物晶格 比如黄宝石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even a relatively complex mineral lattice like topaz,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.85,0:21:25.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由10个左右的原子组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}composed of ten or so atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.32,0:21:27.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也只是相同的原子结构\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can only repeat the identical atomic structure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.99,0:21:29.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不断重复\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:36.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了转换到另一个维度
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.32,0:21:39.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了将它从不断重复的晶格束缚中释放\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to free it from the lattice prison of endless repetition,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:43.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你需要一个可以从任何方向与其它原子相结合的原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you need an atom that can bond in all directions with other atoms like itself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.83,0:21:46.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它也要能与其它不同的原子相结合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as well as with atoms of different kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.17,0:21:56.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看 碳原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Behold the carbon atom...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.71,0:21:59.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上生命不可缺少的元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the essential element for life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.91,0:22:02.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.78,0:22:07.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}碳之所以特殊 是因为它可以一次与最多4种原子结合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carbon is special because it can bond with up to four other atoms at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.52,0:22:10.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它可以与许多其它种类的原子结合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can connect with many different kinds of atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:13.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也包括其它碳原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as well as other carbon atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.29,0:22:14.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它可以弯曲成环状\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can curl into rings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.96,0:22:17.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也可以连成一条线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and string together into chains,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.19,0:22:21.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}组成远比任何一种晶体都复杂的分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}building molecules far more complex than any crystal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.80,0:22:27.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它原子都没有这种灵活性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No other atom has the same flexibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.74,0:22:30.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就算拥有类似化学属性的原子也不行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even atoms that have similar chemical properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.21,0:22:31.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如 硅\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like silicon,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.81,0:22:36.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也无法像碳这样组成丰富多样的分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can't form the amazing variety of molecules built on carbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.98,0:22:38.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种碳基分子 我们称为 蛋白质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The carbon-based molecules we call proteins,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.55,0:22:40.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}组成生命的分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the molecules of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.75,0:22:43.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包含了成千上万的原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}contain literally hundreds of thousands of atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.95,0:22:50.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}碳原子是世界上一切生物分子的支柱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carbon atoms are the backbone of the molecules that make every living thing on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.16,0:22:52.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.66,0:22:55.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是岩石和生物的区别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the difference between rocks and living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.57,0:22:59.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命可以制造出大量的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life can make enormous molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.00,0:23:02.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有着惊人体积和复杂性的分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of stunning size and complexity,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.51,0:23:04.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自由自在地随机应变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}freeing matter to improvise,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.64,0:23:06.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}进化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.67,0:23:08.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至 爱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and even love.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.46,0:23:43.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}孩子的父亲 您别担心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take it easy, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.53,0:23:45.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他并没有真的碰到的她\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He never actually touched her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.97,0:23:49.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日常生活中以原子这个层面上来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In everyday life on our world, on the scale of atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.74,0:23:53.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物体绝对不会相互接触到对方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}material objects never really touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.64,0:23:57.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个原子的中心都有一个原子核\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each atom has a tiny nucleus at its center,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.08,0:24:00.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被力线电子云所包围\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}surrounded by an electron cloud of lines of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.48,0:24:02.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当原子彼此接近时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the atoms approach each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.99,0:24:04.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}男孩的电子云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the boy's electron clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.95,0:24:06.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}推开女孩的电子云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}push away the girl's.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.56,0:24:12.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超过99.9%的原子物质都集中在它的原子核中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}More than 99.9% of the matter of any atom is concentrated in its nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.93,0:24:16.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核被电子云包围\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nucleus is surrounded by an electron cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.40,0:24:18.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电子云形成无形的力场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which produces an invisible field of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.80,0:24:21.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像减震器\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and acts like a shock absorber.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.11,0:24:25.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电子云的结构决定了元素的本质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The configuration of the electron cloud determines the nature of an element.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.78,0:24:28.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以地球上物质的正常情况来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the ordinary course of things here on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.45,0:24:30.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核永远不会彼此接触\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the nuclei never touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.35,0:24:32.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们有接触的感觉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have a sensation of touching,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.45,0:24:35.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那只不过是看不见的力场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that's really just our invisible force fields
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.09,0:24:38.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相互重迭的同时相互排斥\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}overlapping and repelling each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.80,0:24:57.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相较于原子的其它部分 原子核非常小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nucleus is very small compared to the rest of the atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.94,0:25:01.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果原子像这个教堂这么大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If an atom were the size of this cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.98,0:25:06.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核的尺寸也就是那粒灰尘的大小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its nucleus would be the size of that mote of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.99,0:25:13.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子的大部分是空旷的空间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An atom is mostly empty space.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.22,0:25:15.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了理解事物的本质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To understand the nature of matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.96,0:25:17.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们要去更深的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we have to go deeper still,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.96,0:25:20.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}去一个比原子还小10万倍的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a place 100,000 times smaller than the atom:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.00,0:25:23.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是它的原子核\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.17,0:25:30.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中最简单 但又最丰富的原子是氢原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The simplest and most plentiful atom in the cosmos is hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.64,0:25:32.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的原子核只有一个质子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its nucleus is a single proton,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.88,0:25:35.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以它在元素周期表中位于第一位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which makes hydrogen element number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.91,0:25:37.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}围绕着它的云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The clouds that surround it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.75,0:25:42.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是它唯一的电子可以运行的范围\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the realms where the atom's lone electron is permitted to roam.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.72,0:25:45.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核有两个质子时会是什么情况\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What happens when you have a nucleus with two protons?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.99,0:25:47.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}质子相互排斥\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Protons repel each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.66,0:25:49.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了让它们保持在原子核内\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In order to hold them together in a nucleus,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.02,0:25:53.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你还需要另一种粒子 称之 中子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you need other particles called neutrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.23,0:25:57.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的工作是防止质子出轨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their job is to keep the protons from getting out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.27,0:26:02.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们用强大的核引力压制质子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They overwhelm the protons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.27,0:26:05.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核有2个质子的元素排名第2\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A nucleus with two protons is element number two,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.54,0:26:08.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}名曰 氦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}otherwise known as helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.21,0:26:11.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核有6个质子的元素排名第6\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A nucleus with six protons is element number six,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.25,0:26:13.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is carbon,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.21,0:26:16.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命的基石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the fundamental building block of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.35,0:26:19.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金元素的原子核有79个质子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nucleus of a gold atom has 79 protons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.52,0:26:23.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在周围的云中 它们吸引了79个电子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They attract 79 electrons in clouds around it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.39,0:26:25.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光与这些电子的互动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The way light interacts with those electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.69,0:26:28.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是黄金闪光的原因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is what makes gold glitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.29,0:26:31.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核中每增加一个质子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every additional proton in the nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.26,0:26:34.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都需要有足够的中子把它们聚集在一起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}requires enough neutrons to bind them together...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.56,0:26:36.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在一定程度上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Up to a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.23,0:26:40.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你能塞进原子核的中子数量是有上限的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's an upper limit to the number of neutrons you can stuff into a nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.20,0:26:41.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}否则会变得不稳定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before it becomes unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.97,0:26:44.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有个地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I know a place
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.14,0:26:46.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不同原子的原子核\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the nuclei of different atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.21,0:26:48.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能够相互接触\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually do touch each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.26,0:27:10.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳看上去像个实体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sun looks like a solid object,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.77,0:27:12.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但并不是这样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.97,0:27:17.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它把所有的原子都加热到了气态\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's so hot that all its atoms are always in their gaseous state.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.81,0:27:20.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上将原子束缚产生液态和固体的粘合力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The bonds that join atoms to make solids and liquids on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.01,0:27:25.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不足以承受炽热太阳的热量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are not strong enough to withstand the heat of the broiling sun
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.88,0:27:30.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些耀眼气体的弧形气流使地球看上去渺小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those arcing streams of incandescent gas that dwarf the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.95,0:27:36.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其实它们都受到太阳表面之下发射出来的力场的磁力线引导\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are guided by magnetic lines of force that emanate from below the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.16,0:27:38.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳怎么会这么热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why is the sun so hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.69,0:27:40.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为它惊人的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because its own stupendous gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.00,0:27:43.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将原子们积压在一起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is squeezing its atoms together.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.80,0:27:48.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}引力的能量转换成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy of gravity is being transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.44,0:27:50.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}移动原子的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the energy of moving atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.57,0:27:53.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是热的来源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what heat is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.27,0:27:55.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}越到太阳的内部\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The deeper we go into the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.14,0:27:56.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}挤压的力量越大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the greater the squeezing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.94,0:27:59.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}温度也越高\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the higher the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.21,0:28:00.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在太阳的中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the heart of the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.78,0:28:08.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子的移动速度快到 它们碰撞时发生融化 原子核发生接触\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the atoms are moving so fast that when they collide, they fuse. Their nuclei touch.
