Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.31,0:33:01.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如同即将沉船上的老鼠 慌不择路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like rats deserting a sinking ship, the neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.91,0:33:04.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即将爆炸的恒星内部产生的中微子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}produced in the heart of the exploding star
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.41,0:33:06.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以接近光速的速度向外逃逸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}race outward at near the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.98,0:33:10.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几秒内穿过覆盖物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through overlying mass in only a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.99,0:33:13.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是爆炸气体的冲击波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the shock wave of the exploding gas
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.22,0:33:16.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从恒星内部缓缓踱出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}plods along from the center of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.26,0:33:18.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有光速的万分之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at 1/10,000 the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.89,0:33:21.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到最后抵达\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until it finally reaches
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.13,0:33:22.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星的表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star's surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.60,0:33:26.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变成了1987年的超新星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}turning it into supernova 1987a.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.44,0:33:34.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要好几个小时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It took hours for the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.14,0:33:36.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爆炸才能到达表面 然后向外喷发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to reach the surface of the star and blow it wide open,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.75,0:33:38.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将极度炙热的内核炸开\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exposing the super hot core.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.88,0:33:41.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}中微子已经赢在了起跑在线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The neutrinos had an insurmountable head start.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.65,0:33:47.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是为什么闪光会比中微子晚这么多到达地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why the flash of light arrived on earth so much later than the shower of neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.49,0:33:50.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在「野生」中微子被捕获前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before anyone had ever snared the wild neutrino,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.96,0:33:54.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它已经存在于理论物理学家的脑海中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it existed in the mind of a theoretical physicist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.86,0:33:57.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就如同查尔斯・达尔文知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as Charles Darwin knew
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.93,0:34:02.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}必定有一种超级长鼻生物生活在马达加斯加\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there must be an extremely long-nosed creature flying around somewhere in Madagascar
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.54,0:34:06.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一位名叫沃尔夫冈・泡利的20世纪物理学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a 20th-century physicist named Wolfgang Pauli...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.38,0:34:11.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}致力于寻找一种微粒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was desperately seeking a particle
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.35,0:34:13.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用来拯救现代物理学的支柱之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to rescue one of the pillars of modern physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.65,0:34:16.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能量守恒定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the law of the conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.83,0:34:27.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我为什么没有退缩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So why didn't I flinch?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.89,0:34:31.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为科学定律与其它人类活动的根本区别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because the laws of science differ fundamentally from those of other human endeavors
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.03,0:34:35.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要将一种设想变成科学定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In order for an idea to become a scientific law,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:37.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}必须要无懈可击\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it has to unbreakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.40,0:34:40.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是为何我愿意赌上我的脸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why I was willing to bet this face
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.17,0:34:43.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来证明能量守恒定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the laws of conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.08,0:34:45.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你在家自己尝试\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, if you try this at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.51,0:34:48.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}千万小心不要推这个球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}take care not to give the cannonball a push.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.51,0:34:50.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那会增加能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's adding energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.15,0:34:52.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这球肯定会回来造成伤害\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the ball will surely come back and do some damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.72,0:34:55.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要像这样轻轻放手\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You just have to let it go, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.92,0:34:58.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}抬起这个球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By lifting the ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.26,0:34:59.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你给它势能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you give it gravitational energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.99,0:35:02.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使它可能坠落并且加速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the potential to fall and accelerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.99,0:35:06.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}球在弧度底部时速度达到最大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cannonball is going fastest when it's at the bottom of its arc
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.23,0:35:07.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那个时候\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.90,0:35:12.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它把所有的势能转化成动能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's converted all of its gravitational energy to the energy of motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.17,0:35:14.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}摇摆时 球不断转换能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it swings, the cannonball is constantly exchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.87,0:35:17.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从一种转换到另一种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of these two kinds of energy for the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.11,0:35:20.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是能量的总量保持不变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the total amount of energy remains constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.34,0:35:23.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是能量守恒定律的例子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's an example of the law of conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.71,0:35:26.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}放开球的那刻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once the cannonball is released,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.18,0:35:29.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就无法获得更多的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it can never gain more energy than it had to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.25,0:35:32.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它不可能飞过来打到我的鼻子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has no way to fly up and break my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.59,0:35:36.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能量这笔账永远是平衡的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy accounting books are always strictly balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.59,0:35:38.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}做不得假\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no such thing as cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.96,0:35:40.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在20世纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So in the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:44.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当科学家首次精确测量出原子的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when physicists first calculated the energy of atoms precisely,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.20,0:35:45.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们惊讶的发现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they were startled to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.47,0:35:47.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}违背这个定律的情况\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an apparent violation of this law.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.07,0:35:52.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们发现在一些放射性原子中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They found that in some radioactive atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.58,0:35:55.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子核自发的喷出一个电子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the nucleus can spontaneously eject an electron.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.98,0:35:59.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将原子转变成另一种元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This transforms the atom into a different element.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.55,0:36:02.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物理学家迷惑了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The physicists were mystified.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.12,0:36:04.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}逃逸电子的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy of the escaped electron
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.22,0:36:06.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}加上新元素的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}plus that of the new element
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.22,0:36:09.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}少于原有原子核的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}adds up to less than the energy in the original nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.56,0:36:11.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}定律指出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the law says,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.46,0:36:14.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能量既不会凭空产生 也不会凭空消失\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"thou shall not destroy or create energy."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.40,0:36:17.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那么那些能量去了哪里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So where did the missing energy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.27,0:36:19.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1930年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1930...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.44,0:36:21.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沃尔夫冈・泡利预测\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wolfgang Pauli predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.00,0:36:24.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一定有一种未知的微粒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there must be an undiscovered particle,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.14,0:36:26.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带走了这些能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one that makes off with the missing energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.61,0:36:29.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时 沃尔夫冈・泡利感叹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the time, Pauli lamented
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.41,0:36:32.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如此微小的虚幻微粒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that such a phantom particle might be so minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.85,0:36:34.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}迅速而难以琢磨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}swift and evasive
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.78,0:36:37.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能永远都探测不到了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as to forever defy detection.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.85,0:36:41.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好在那只是他罕有的一次错误预测\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that was a rare failure of his imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.29,0:36:43.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为科学家总是不断\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because science is always searching
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.49,0:36:45.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}寻找探索的新方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a way to go deeper still.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.36,0:36:47.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几十年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A generation later,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.30,0:36:49.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在核反应堆的辐射中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pauli's neutrinos were actually detected for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.66,0:36:52.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}中微子第一次被人们探测到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in radiation from a nuclear reactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.27,0:36:56.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}虽然很艰难 但从那之后我们不断找到更多的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we've been finding them, with difficulty, ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.20,0:36:59.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如今 有些科学家们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are scientists today
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.11,0:37:02.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尝试利用那些中微子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who are trying to find a way to ride those neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.38,0:37:05.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来研究时间的起源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the way back to the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.38,0:37:13.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一起去看看他们的成就  那是一面永恒之墙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'll go as far as they have gone to come up against the wall of forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.65,0:37:25.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}永恒之墙并不新鲜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The wall of forever is nothing new.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.42,0:37:27.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的祖先也遇到过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our ancestors came up against it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.39,0:37:30.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎就在他们第一次开始想象时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}almost as soon as they first started imagining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.53,0:37:35.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几千年前 公元前13世纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A million dawns ago, in the 13th century bc,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.33,0:37:38.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}埃及人建造了阿布辛贝勒神庙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Egyptian built this temple at Abu Simbel
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.87,0:37:40.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}纪念法老王拉美西斯二世\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to honor the Pharaoh Ramses II,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.94,0:37:44.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这里留下了四座巨大的石像\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depicted here in four colossal statues.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.17,0:37:50.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这位伟大君主之上真正的王者其实是鹰首太阳神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Reigning even above even this mighty king is the falcon-headed Ra-Harakhti
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.11,0:37:52.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳之神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}God of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.79,0:38:00.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这座神庙被设计成每年只有两次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The temple was designed so that the light from the rising sun
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.69,0:38:04.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旭日的霞光金辉才会射入神殿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could only enter the sanctuary on two days every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.03,0:38:08.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当光线照进神庙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the rays enter the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.06,0:38:11.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在贯穿整个神殿前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they burnish the statues of the gods with their golden light
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.70,0:38:15.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日光使众神的石像闪耀着金色的光芒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before penetrating the sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.70,0:38:19.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是 仍有一位神的石像依然处在阴影中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even then, one God remains in shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.71,0:38:22.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}普塔 创造之神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ptah, lord of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.21,0:38:27.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}彷佛暗示宇宙的起源注定永远神秘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as if the origin of the universe must forever be concealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.99,0:38:33.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感受阳光照在脸上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Feel the sun on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.82,0:38:36.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使你温暖的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy that warms you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.42,0:38:39.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来自几千万年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}began its journey some ten million years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.59,0:38:41.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳的核心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the heart of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.73,0:38:44.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与中微子不同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike neutrinos,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.80,0:38:46.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}质子需要\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the photons needed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.63,0:38:49.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这么久的时间才能从核心到达表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that long to work their way out from the core to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.64,0:38:51.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.67,0:38:55.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为它们与太阳的原子每秒发生几十亿次的碰撞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because they were colliding billions of times per second with the sun's atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.01,0:38:59.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每次撞击都将它们推向不同的方向\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every collision sending them off in a random direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.91,0:39:01.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们一旦到达表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But once they finally reached the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.91,0:39:05.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们就彻底解放 以光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they were free to dash nonstop, at the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.09,0:39:10.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只用区区8分20秒 就来到你的面前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a mere eight minutes and 20 seconds from the sun to you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.82,0:39:14.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一千万岁高龄的阳光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ten-million-year-old light on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.33,0:39:23.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当那光离开太阳核心时 又是怎么的景象呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What was happening when that light left the heart of the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.87,0:39:30.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙年历将宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmic calendar compresses
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.94,0:39:33.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}整整138亿年的历史\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the entire 13.8 billion year history
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.78,0:39:35.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}压缩到一年的时间内\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the universe into a single year.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.88,0:39:39.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个月代表10亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every month represents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.45,0:39:42.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一天就是4千万年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every day, about 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.35,0:39:45.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙的历史如此悠久 在年历上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is so old that, on the cosmic calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.62,0:39:49.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1千万年前 也只不过是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ten million years ago only takes us back as far as...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.39,0:39:55.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这一年的最后一天的下午6点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}6:00 P.M. on the last evening of the last day of the year
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.90,0:39:57.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那我们呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.50,0:39:59.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类还没开始进化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Humans had yet to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.37,0:40:01.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1千万年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ten million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.14,0:40:03.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的祖先还是类人猿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our ancestors were anthropoid apes,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.57,0:40:05.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}活跃在非洲的丛林中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}swinging through the trees of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.51,0:40:08.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对我们来说 1千万年好像很久远\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To us, ten million years seems like a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.01,0:40:11.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是对于宇宙来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's only the length of an afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.42,0:40:13.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那只不过是半天而已\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the timescale of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.22,0:40:22.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}45亿年前 太阳开始放出光芒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sun began fusing hydrogen 4,500 million years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.19,0:40:25.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙历上的8月31号\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}August 31 on the cosmic calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.93,0:40:27.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的银河系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our milky way galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.00,0:40:31.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大约100亿岁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is about 10,000 million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.10,0:40:36.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第一个星系比它还早几十亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first galaxies formed about a few billion years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.21,0:40:40.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有东西阻挡我们回到更远的过去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something keeps me from going any further back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.18,0:40:42.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是什么呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.85,0:40:47.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是光与时间的本质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the nature of light and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.75,0:40:50.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为光的速度有限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because light travels at a finite speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.95,0:40:55.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们所看到的宇宙 其实只是过去的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to look across space is to look back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.86,0:41:01.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看得越远\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the farther we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.03,0:41:03.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到的光越古老\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the older the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.87,0:41:08.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是我们所能看到宇宙历史上最古老的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is as far back in the history of the cosmos as we can see with light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.70,0:41:11.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是宇宙刚诞生的样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a baby picture of universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.14,0:41:14.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有38万岁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it was only 380,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.24,0:41:19.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙历上最初的15分钟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's 15 minutes into January 1 on the cosmic calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.91,0:41:25.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们用微波望远镜看向宇宙的尽头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we look as far as we can see in any direction using microwave telescopes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.09,0:41:26.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到的就是这样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this is what we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.55,0:41:29.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大爆炸留下的光晕\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the glow left over from the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.89,0:41:33.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想象一下 可观测宇宙的所有物质和能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine that all the matter and energy of the observable universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.79,0:41:38.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都被浓缩成这样的大小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was concentrated into something no larger than this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.10,0:41:41.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是当时宇宙的大小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the size of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.00,0:41:47.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当它只有一分之一万亿岁时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it was a trillionth of a trillionth of a trillionth of a second old
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.41,0:41:50.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几千亿个星系的物质与能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the matter and energy of the hundred billion galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.98,0:41:54.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如今扩展到方圆几十亿光年的范围\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}now splayed out across the billions of light-years
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.08,0:41:58.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}曾经都被禁锢在这个弹珠大小的东西内\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were once pent up in something the size of a marble
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.45,0:42:02.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你能想象出那颗弹珠有多紧密吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can you imagine how tightly packed that marble must have been?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.42,0:42:05.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}稠密得使任何光都无法穿过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Far too dense for any kind of light to move through it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.29,0:42:09.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这阻碍不了中微子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but no obstacle for the likes of neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.09,0:42:11.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大爆炸必定产生了数量惊人的中微子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The big bang must have produced stupendous numbers of neutrinos,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.00,0:42:15.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们顺畅地穿过那些紧密得难以置信的物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which flew unhindered through that inconceivable crush of matter
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.70,0:42:18.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使它们几乎无法被探测的最关键因素是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The very thing that makes them almost impossible to detect
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.94,0:42:25.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们可以穿过遮掩时间起源的厚重幕布\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is what allows neutrinos to sail through the curtain that conceals the beginning of time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.71,0:42:27.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们在哪里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where are they now?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.31,0:42:28.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这里 在那里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are here, they're there,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.88,0:42:31.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中无处不在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}everywhere throughout the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.12,0:42:33.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙诞生时中微子就在你的内心深处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neutrinos from creation are within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.02,0:42:37.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从一个弹珠\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From a marble...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.29,0:42:39.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到整个宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.03,0:42:56.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一条泰利斯和德谟克利特2500年前带我们走上的路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the road that Thales and Democritus put us on some 2,500 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.17,0:42:58.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无尽的探索之路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a road of endless searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.24,0:43:01.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不断的有条不紊的探索新的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a relentless, systematic hunt for new worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.58,0:43:04.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且不断加深对自然的理解\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and an ever-deepening understanding of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.68,0:43:12.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你们中有人会接过火炬 带领我们走上一条更宽广的大路吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Who among you will pick up that torch and take us down that next stretch of road?
